questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2015&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) were adopted by all United Nations Member States during the &lt;strong&gt;UN Sustainable Development Summit&lt;/strong&gt; held in New York.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The adoption of the SDGs took place on &lt;strong&gt;25 September 2015&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The SDGs consist of &lt;strong&gt;17 goals&lt;/strong&gt; aimed at addressing global challenges such as poverty, inequality, climate change, environmental degradation, peace, and justice.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The SDGs are part of the 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development, which provides a shared blueprint for peace and prosperity for people and the planet, now and into the future.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Millennium Development Goals (MDGs):&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The SDGs succeeded the Millennium Development Goals, which were eight goals set to be achieved by 2015.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The MDGs focused on a narrower set of issues such as eradicating extreme poverty and hunger, achieving universal primary education, and reducing child mortality.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This agenda was adopted by all UN Member States in 2015.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It includes 17 SDGs and 169 targets intended to be achieved by the year 2030.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The agenda emphasizes a holistic approach to sustainable development for both developed and developing countries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnerships for the Goals (SDG 17):&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This goal emphasizes the need for global partnerships to achieve the ambitious targets of the SDGs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It focuses on strengthening the means of implementation and revitalizing the global partnership for sustainable development.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leave No One Behind:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A core principle of the SDGs is to ensure that no one is left behind in the journey towards sustainable development.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This includes addressing the needs of the most vulnerable and ensuring inclusivity and equity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 5 to 11&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Citizenship&lt;/strong&gt; is listed in the &lt;strong&gt;Union List&lt;/strong&gt; under the Constitution. The Constitution does not define the term &amp;lsquo;citizen&amp;rsquo; but details of various categories of persons who are entitled to citizenship are given in Part 2 &lt;strong&gt;(Articles 5 to 11)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Article 5: Citizenship at the commencement of the Constitution At the commencement of this Constitution every person who has his domicile in the territory of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Article 6: It provided rights of citizenship of certain persons who have migrated to India from Pakistan.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Article 7: Provided Rights of citizenship of certain migrants to Pakistan.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Article 8: Provided Rights of citizenship of certain persons of Indian origin residing outside India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Article 9: Provided that if any person voluntarily acquired the citizenship of a foreign State will no longer be a citizen of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Article 10: It says that every person who is or is deemed to be a citizen of India under any of the foregoing provisions of this Part shall, subject to the provisions of any law that may be made by Parliament, continue to be such citizen.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Article 11: It empowers Parliament to make any provision with respect to the acquisition and termination of citizenship and all matters relating to it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Copper and Bronze&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The tools and implements of the &lt;strong&gt;Harappan civilisation&lt;/strong&gt; were primarily made of &lt;strong&gt;Copper and Bronze&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;During the Harappan era, which is part of the &lt;strong&gt;Chalcolithic Age (Copper Age)&lt;/strong&gt;, the use of metals such as copper and bronze marked technological advancements.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Copper&lt;/strong&gt; was one of the first metals to be used by humans, and the Harappan people utilized it to craft tools, weapons, and ornaments.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bronze&lt;/strong&gt;, an alloy of copper and tin, was used to create more durable tools, weapons, and artifacts such as statues and seals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The famous &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Dancing Girl&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; statue found at Mohenjo-Daro is an excellent example of Harappan craftsmanship using bronze.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This technological expertise demonstrates the Harappan civilization&amp;#39;s advanced knowledge of &lt;strong&gt;metallurgy&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The use of these metals was facilitated by the availability of raw materials, such as copper from the &lt;strong&gt;Khetri mines&lt;/strong&gt; in Rajasthan and tin from areas like Afghanistan.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The tools and implements made of copper and bronze were used for a variety of purposes, including &lt;strong&gt;agriculture, hunting, and domestic work&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Copper&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Copper&lt;/strong&gt; was widely used during the Chalcolithic Age, marking the transition from the Stone Age to the Metal Age.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a soft metal, making it suitable for crafting simple tools and ornaments.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Harappans sourced copper from regions like &lt;strong&gt;Khetri (Rajasthan)&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Baluchistan&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bronze&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bronze&lt;/strong&gt; is an alloy of copper and tin, providing greater hardness and durability than pure copper.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It was used to create &lt;strong&gt;weapons, tools, statues, and seals&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The famous &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Dancing Girl&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; artifact showcases the Harappan expertise in bronze casting.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Iron&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Iron&lt;/strong&gt; was not used during the Harappan civilisation, as it belonged to the &lt;strong&gt;Iron Age&lt;/strong&gt;, which came after the Bronze Age.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The use of iron tools and weapons became prominent in later periods, such as the &lt;strong&gt;Vedic Age&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Recycle Bin&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the &lt;strong&gt;Windows Operating System&lt;/strong&gt;, deleted files are temporarily moved to the &lt;strong&gt;Recycle Bin&lt;/strong&gt; by default instead of being permanently erased.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This feature allows users to &lt;strong&gt;recover files&lt;/strong&gt; that were accidentally deleted.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Recycle Bin&lt;/strong&gt; acts as a holding area, providing an opportunity to restore items to their original location.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Files in the Recycle Bin remain there until the user decides to &lt;strong&gt;permanently delete&lt;/strong&gt; them by emptying the bin or until the storage limit of the bin is reached.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The storage size of the Recycle Bin is typically a &lt;strong&gt;percentage of the total disk space&lt;/strong&gt;, and this limit can be customized by the user.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Items in the Recycle Bin retain their original file properties, such as &lt;strong&gt;file type, size, and modification date&lt;/strong&gt;, until they are permanently removed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Recycle Bin is located on the &lt;strong&gt;desktop interface&lt;/strong&gt; of Windows, making it easily accessible to users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Downloads Folder&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Downloads folder&lt;/strong&gt; in Windows OS is a default location where files downloaded from the internet are saved.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is not associated with deleted files but with &lt;strong&gt;retrieving downloaded content&lt;/strong&gt; like documents, videos, or software.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Users can manually move or delete items from the Downloads folder.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cloud&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The term &lt;strong&gt;The Cloud&lt;/strong&gt; refers to cloud storage services like &lt;strong&gt;Google Drive, OneDrive, or Dropbox&lt;/strong&gt;, which are used for storing data online.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Deleted files are not automatically sent to the cloud unless they are synced with a cloud service.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Files stored in the cloud may have their own &lt;strong&gt;recycle bin or trash folder&lt;/strong&gt; depending on the service provider.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;They are permanently erased&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Files in Windows are not permanently erased by default when deleted. They are first moved to the &lt;strong&gt;Recycle Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;However, files can be permanently deleted using &lt;strong&gt;Shift + Delete&lt;/strong&gt; or by emptying the Recycle Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alauddin Khalji&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alauddin Khalji&lt;/strong&gt;, the second ruler of the Khalji dynasty, introduced the market control system, also known as &lt;strong&gt;Diwan-i-Riyasat&lt;/strong&gt;, as part of his administrative reforms.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The primary aim of this system was to regulate prices of essential goods, including food grains, clothing, and military supplies, to ensure affordability and maintain economic stability.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Alauddin Khalji established separate markets for different commodities, such as &lt;strong&gt;grains, cloth, and horses&lt;/strong&gt;. These were monitored by market officers called &lt;strong&gt;Shahna-i-Mandi&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Sultan enforced strict price controls by fixing the cost of goods and services. Traders and merchants were required to sell their goods at government-mandated prices.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To prevent hoarding and black marketing, Alauddin Khalji implemented severe punishments for violators. Spies were employed to monitor market activities and report any misconduct.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alauddin Khalji&amp;#39;s Reforms:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He introduced several administrative measures to strengthen his empire, including &lt;strong&gt;taxation reforms&lt;/strong&gt; and land revenue administration.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The market control system was part of his broader strategy to maintain a large standing army and ensure the kingdom&amp;#39;s economic stability.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Control System:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This system ensured that the price of goods was affordable for common people and soldiers. For instance, the price of grains was fixed at a lower rate to ensure food security for all.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Traders were required to register themselves, and stockpiling or overpricing was strictly prohibited.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role of Shahna-i-Mandi:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Shahna-i-Mandi was responsible for enforcing price regulations and ensuring that no trader cheated customers or violated the set price limits.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They conducted regular inspections and maintained records of stock levels and prices in the market.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact of the Market Control System:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The system ensured the availability of essential goods at fixed prices, which benefited both the military and the common population.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;However, these strict measures also led to hardships for traders and merchants, as they were forced to sell goods at lower prices, reducing their profits.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comparison with Other Rulers:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Iltutmish:&lt;/strong&gt; He was the first ruler of the Delhi Sultanate to introduce the silver &lt;strong&gt;Tanka&lt;/strong&gt; and copper &lt;strong&gt;Jital&lt;/strong&gt; coins but did not introduce a market control system.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Balban:&lt;/strong&gt; He focused on strengthening the Sultanate through centralized administration and military reforms, rather than economic control measures.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Firoz Shah Tughlaq:&lt;/strong&gt; He is known for his irrigation projects, taxation reforms, and welfare measures but did not implement a market control system like Alauddin Khalji.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Significance of the Market Control System:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It was primarily aimed at maintaining a well-equipped and well-fed army, which was crucial for Alauddin Khalji&amp;#39;s expansionist policies.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The system highlighted the Sultan&amp;#39;s administrative efficiency and his efforts to balance economic stability with military needs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Challenges in Implementation:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While the system was effective during Alauddin Khalji&amp;#39;s reign, it faced difficulties in sustaining itself after his death due to lack of strong enforcement mechanisms.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meghalaya&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The highest rainfall in India is at Cherrapunji(Present name Sohra) in Mawsynram village of Meghalaya state.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Average rainfall of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Cherrapunji is 11,777 mm or 463.7 in.&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:500px;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;tbody&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RAINFALL REGIONS IN INDIA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rainfall(cm)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;More than 200 cm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td&gt;
				&lt;ul&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assam Hill, Southern Part of Kerala, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Western slope of Western ghats, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The coastal plain of Kerala, Karnataka.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;/ul&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Between 100 to 200 cm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td&gt;
				&lt;ul&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The middle valley in Bihar, Jharkhand, West Bengal, Odisha, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part of the Western ghat, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northern Part of Andra Pradesh, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southern Part of Tamil Nadu.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;/ul&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Between 50 to 100 cm&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td&gt;
				&lt;ul&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Upper Ganga valley &amp;amp; Eastern Rajasthan, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parts of Punjab &amp;amp; Hariyana, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parts of Jammu &amp;amp; Kashmir.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;/ul&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Less than 50 cm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td&gt;
				&lt;ul&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Western Rajasthan, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ladakh in Jammu &amp;amp; Kashmir.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;/ul&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/tbody&gt;
	&lt;/table&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pulakesin II.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pulakesin II&amp;nbsp;defeated Harshavardhana when he invaded the Chalukya kingdom in the Deccan.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Pulakeshin II&lt;/span&gt;, the King of the Chalukya dynasty defeated Harshavardhana when he sought&amp;nbsp;to enlarge his Empire into the southern peninsula of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He defeated Harshavardhana on the banks of the &lt;strong&gt;Narmada &lt;/strong&gt;river in &lt;strong&gt;618-619&amp;nbsp;AD.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Aihole inscription was written by the &lt;strong&gt;Ravikirti&lt;/strong&gt;, court poet of Chalukya King, &lt;strong&gt;Pulakesin II&lt;/strong&gt; who reigned from &lt;strong&gt;610 to 642 CE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Chalukya dynasty:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It&amp;nbsp;lasted from&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;543 A.D. to 755 A.D.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Pulakesin I&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;was the founder of the Chalukya dynasty. He established a small kingdom with&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Vatapi or Badami&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;as its capital.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Western Chalukyas ruled over an extensive area in the&amp;nbsp;Deccan for about two centuries after which the Rashtrakutas became&amp;nbsp;powerful.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The family of Western Chalukyas had its offshoots like&amp;nbsp;the Eastern&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Chalukyas of Vengi&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Chalukyas of Kalyani.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Kirtivarman II&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;was the last of the rulers of the Chalukyas.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;defeated by Dantidurga&lt;/span&gt;, the founder of the Rashtrakuta dynasty.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Occurrence of Chauri Chaura incident&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Non-Cooperation Movement was suspended by Gandhi in February 1922 after the violent Chauri Chaura incident in Gorakhpur, Uttar Pradesh.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;On February 4, 1922, a clash between protesters and police led to the mob setting a police station ablaze, killing 22 policemen.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Gandhi believed in non-violence as the core philosophy of the movement, and the Chauri Chaura incident contradicted this principle.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He feared that the continuation of the movement might lead to more violent outbreaks and derail the original purpose of achieving independence through peaceful means.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The suspension of the movement showcased Gandhi&amp;rsquo;s commitment to his principle of non-violence even at the cost of halting the struggle for independence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;British promises of reforms&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;During the Non-Cooperation Movement, the British government attempted to pacify Indians by promising minor reforms under the Montagu-Chelmsford Reforms (Government of India Act 1919).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;However, these reforms were widely criticized for being inadequate and incapable of fulfilling the aspirations of Indians for self-governance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These promises did not play a direct role in Gandhi&amp;rsquo;s decision to suspend the movement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Arrest of national leaders&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The British administration arrested several leaders during the Non-Cooperation Movement to suppress the agitation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;However, the arrests were a regular part of the colonial government&amp;rsquo;s strategy and did not directly impact Gandhi&amp;rsquo;s decision to halt the movement.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The arrest of Gandhi himself occurred later, in March 1922, after the suspension of the movement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Failure of Khilafat support&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Khilafat Movement, which aimed to protect the Ottoman Caliphate, was supported by Gandhi to unite Hindus and Muslims in the struggle against British rule.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While the Khilafat Movement eventually lost momentum due to changes in Turkey and waning enthusiasm, this was not the immediate cause of suspending the Non-Cooperation Movement.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Gandhi&amp;rsquo;s decision was primarily driven by the Chauri Chaura incident, not the failure of Khilafat support.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main Theme: Non-Cooperation Movement&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Non-Cooperation Movement, launched by Mahatma Gandhi in 1920, was a mass protest against British colonial rule.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It involved boycotting British goods, institutions, and titles while promoting swadeshi products and indigenous education.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The movement marked a significant phase in India&amp;rsquo;s struggle for independence, showcasing Gandhi&amp;rsquo;s leadership and the power of mass mobilization.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adhai-Din-Ka-Jhonpra is situated in Ajmer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adhai-Din-Ka-Jhonpra&lt;/strong&gt; is one of the oldest mosques in India, located in the city of &lt;strong&gt;Ajmer, Rajasthan&lt;/strong&gt;. It is a significant historical and architectural landmark.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The mosque was originally a &lt;strong&gt;Sanskrit college&lt;/strong&gt; built during the reign of &lt;strong&gt;Prithviraj Chauhan&lt;/strong&gt;, and it was later converted into a mosque by &lt;strong&gt;Qutub-ud-Din Aibak&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;1192 CE&lt;/strong&gt; after the conquest of Ajmer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The name &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Adhai-Din&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; translates to &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Two-and-a-half days&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; in Hindi, which is derived from the legend that it was constructed in just two-and-a-half days.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The mosque is known for its impressive architecture, which combines &lt;strong&gt;Indo-Islamic&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Hindu styles&lt;/strong&gt;. Its intricate carvings, arches, and domes showcase the craftsmanship of the period.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The site is a popular tourist destination, attracting visitors for its historical importance and architectural beauty. It is also considered a symbol of the cultural amalgamation of India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;History of Adhai-Din-Ka-Jhonpra:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The mosque was built by &lt;strong&gt;Qutub-ud-Din Aibak&lt;/strong&gt;, the founder of the &lt;strong&gt;Delhi Sultanate&lt;/strong&gt;, during his reign after defeating &lt;strong&gt;Prithviraj Chauhan&lt;/strong&gt; in the second battle of Tarain.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It was initially a &lt;strong&gt;Hindu temple and Sanskrit college&lt;/strong&gt;, which was repurposed into a mosque. The transformation reflects the transition between Hindu and Islamic influence in the region.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architectural Features:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The mosque displays a unique blend of &lt;strong&gt;Hindu temple architecture&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Islamic motifs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It has &lt;strong&gt;ornate pillars&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;intricate carvings&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;floral designs&lt;/strong&gt;, which are typical of Indian craftsmanship, while the arches and domes represent Islamic styles.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;main prayer hall&lt;/strong&gt; is supported by intricately carved pillars, showcasing the fusion of cultural elements.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tourist Importance:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Adhai-Din-Ka-Jhonpra is a major attraction in &lt;strong&gt;Ajmer&lt;/strong&gt; and is often visited along with &lt;strong&gt;Ajmer Sharif Dargah&lt;/strong&gt;, another significant Islamic site in the city.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It serves as an example of &lt;strong&gt;India&amp;#39;s rich cultural history&lt;/strong&gt; and attracts history enthusiasts and architectural admirers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Nearby Attractions:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ajmer Sharif Dargah:&lt;/strong&gt; The tomb of the Sufi saint &lt;strong&gt;Moinuddin Chishti&lt;/strong&gt;, a revered pilgrimage site for Muslims.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anasagar Lake:&lt;/strong&gt; A scenic artificial lake constructed by &lt;strong&gt;Anaji Chauhan&lt;/strong&gt;, offering beautiful views and recreational activities.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pushkar:&lt;/strong&gt; Located near Ajmer, Pushkar is famous for its &lt;strong&gt;Brahma Temple&lt;/strong&gt; and the annual &lt;strong&gt;Pushkar Camel Fair&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ajmer:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ajmer is a historic city in &lt;strong&gt;Rajasthan&lt;/strong&gt;, known for its rich cultural heritage and religious significance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The city is a blend of Hindu and Islamic influences, evident in its historical monuments and traditions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qutub-ud-Din Aibak:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was the founder of the &lt;strong&gt;Delhi Sultanate&lt;/strong&gt; and the first ruler of the &lt;strong&gt;Mamluk Dynasty&lt;/strong&gt; in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He is also credited with starting the construction of the &lt;strong&gt;Qutub Minar&lt;/strong&gt; in Delhi.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MSConfig&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MSConfig (Microsoft System Configuration Utility)&lt;/strong&gt; is a system utility to troubleshoot the Microsoft Windows startup process.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It can enable or disable software, device drivers, and Windows services that run at startup, which can help to identify problematic processes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MSConfig can be used to configure how the computer starts and diagnose startup issues, improving the system&amp;#39;s boot time and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It provides several startup options, including Normal Startup, Diagnostic Startup, and Selective Startup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disk Management&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This utility is used for managing disk drives and the partitions associated with them.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It allows users to create, delete, format, and resize partitions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It also provides options for initializing new disks and setting up RAID configurations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Task Manager&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Task Manager allows users to view and manage running applications and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It provides information about the system&amp;#39;s performance, including CPU and memory usage.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It can be used to end unresponsive programs and monitor system activity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Device Manager&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Device Manager is used to view and control the hardware attached to the computer.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It allows users to install, update, and roll back drivers for hardware devices.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It also provides options for enabling, disabling, and troubleshooting hardware components.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tertiary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;284&quot; data-start=&quot;78&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tourism&lt;/strong&gt; is a part of the &lt;strong&gt;tertiary sector&lt;/strong&gt; of the economy. It involves providing services such as accommodation, transportation, entertainment, and guidance to tourists.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;605&quot; data-start=&quot;482&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;tertiary sector&lt;/strong&gt;, also known as the &lt;strong&gt;service sector&lt;/strong&gt;, focuses on delivering services rather than goods. Examples include healthcare, education, financial services, and tourism.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;692&quot; data-start=&quot;610&quot;&gt;Tourism in India supports &lt;strong&gt;economic growth&lt;/strong&gt; by contributing to GDP, generating employment, and promoting regional development. &lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct option is Tertiary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1041&quot; data-start=&quot;850&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Indian tourism industry&lt;/strong&gt; also attracts foreign investments and enhances cultural exchange, making it a critical component of the service economy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Economic Sectors:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2410&quot; data-start=&quot;2195&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary sector:&lt;/strong&gt; Involves extraction of natural resources, such as agriculture, fishing, and mining.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2684&quot; data-start=&quot;2415&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Secondary sector:&lt;/strong&gt; Includes industries that process raw materials and manufacture goods, such as factories and construction.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2860&quot; data-start=&quot;2735&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tertiary sector:&lt;/strong&gt; Focuses on services like tourism, healthcare, education, banking, and entertainment.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3071&quot; data-start=&quot;2865&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quinary sector:&lt;/strong&gt; Involves high-level decision-making and research, typically by government officials or top executives.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tourism in India:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3250&quot; data-start=&quot;3076&quot;&gt;India is a popular destination for cultural, historical, and nature tourism, with sites such as &lt;strong&gt;Taj Mahal, Jaipur, Kerala backwaters, Goa beaches&lt;/strong&gt;, and Himalayan treks.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3402&quot; data-start=&quot;3301&quot;&gt;The tourism industry contributes around &lt;strong&gt;9.2% of India&amp;rsquo;s GDP&lt;/strong&gt; (as per World Travel and Tourism Council data).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3580&quot; data-start=&quot;3407&quot;&gt;It provides employment to millions, directly and indirectly, supporting sectors like transportation, hospitality, and retail.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Government Initiatives:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;4636&quot; data-start=&quot;4411&quot;&gt;Schemes like &lt;strong&gt;Swadesh Darshan&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Incredible India&lt;/strong&gt; aim to promote Indian tourism globally and improve infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;4761&quot; data-start=&quot;4641&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;e-Visa:&lt;/strong&gt; India offers e-Visa facilities to tourists from multiple countries, simplifying travel processes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Environmental and Cultural Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;5043&quot; data-start=&quot;4817&quot;&gt;Tourism promotes awareness of &lt;strong&gt;India&amp;rsquo;s diverse culture&lt;/strong&gt;, heritage, and traditions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;5259&quot; data-start=&quot;5048&quot;&gt;It encourages conservation efforts for historical monuments, wildlife, and natural resources.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;Outer Core&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outer Core:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Earth&amp;#39;s outer core is composed of molten iron and nickel.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The convection currents in this liquid outer core, combined with the rotation of the Earth, generate electric currents.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These electric currents create the Earth&amp;#39;s magnetic field through a process known as the geodynamo.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The fluid motion within the outer core is crucial to producing the magnetic field that protects the Earth from solar and cosmic radiation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crust:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Earth&amp;#39;s crust is the outermost solid layer where we live, comprising solid rocks and minerals.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is not involved in generating the Earth&amp;rsquo;s magnetic field.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The crust is far too thin and lacks the necessary dynamic properties to contribute to geomagnetic processes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inner Core:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The inner core is solid and composed mainly of iron and nickel.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While it is mostly responsible for intense pressure and temperature, it does not generate the magnetic field directly.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The movement within the outer core is crucial, and the solid inner core primarily influences the dynamics of the outer core through its motion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mantle:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The mantle lies between the crust and the core and mainly consists of silicate minerals.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It handles thermal and mechanical properties but does not generate the Earth&amp;#39;s magnetic field.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Convection currents within the mantle are significant for plate tectonics but not for geomagnetic processes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Persian and Hindavi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amir Khusrau&lt;/strong&gt; was a renowned &lt;strong&gt;Sufi musician, poet, and scholar&lt;/strong&gt; in medieval India, often referred to as the &amp;quot;Parrot of India&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He is known for his significant contributions to &lt;strong&gt;Persian&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Hindavi&lt;/strong&gt; (an early form of Hindi and Urdu), which laid the foundation for the development of Urdu language.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He wrote extensively in &lt;strong&gt;Persian&lt;/strong&gt;, composing various poems, riddles, and prose, which enriched Indo-Persian literature.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Khusrau is credited with introducing Hindavi into his works, blending Persian and local Indian languages, creating a fusion of linguistic traditions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;His works in &lt;strong&gt;Hindavi&lt;/strong&gt; include riddles, songs, and couplets, making him a pioneer in developing the vernacular tradition in Indian literature.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Persian Language:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Persian&lt;/strong&gt; was widely used as the court language during the Delhi Sultanate and Mughal period.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Amir Khusrau&amp;#39;s Persian poetry includes &lt;strong&gt;Ghazals, Masnavis, and Rubaiyat&lt;/strong&gt;, showcasing themes of love, spirituality, and philosophy.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His Persian works include &lt;strong&gt;Tughluq Nama&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Qiran-us-Sa&amp;rsquo;dain&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Khazain-ul-Futuh&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Persian became a medium for administrative purposes and literary creativity during Khusrau&amp;#39;s era.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hindavi Language:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hindavi&lt;/strong&gt; was an early form of Hindi and Urdu, and Amir Khusrau is regarded as one of its early proponents.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Khusrau&amp;#39;s Hindavi works include riddles, folk songs, and couplets that reflect the socio-cultural milieu of his time.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His Hindavi compositions were enjoyed by both the elite and the common people, popularizing local dialects in literature.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Hindavi later evolved into modern Hindi and Urdu, forming the basis of contemporary North Indian languages.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amir Khusrau&amp;rsquo;s Legacy:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He is credited with creating the &lt;strong&gt;qawwali&lt;/strong&gt; genre, blending Persian and Indian musical traditions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Khusrau introduced new instruments like the &lt;strong&gt;tabla&lt;/strong&gt; and popularized the sitar during his time.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His contributions to literature and music earned him the title of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Father of Urdu Literature&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was a disciple of Sufi saint &lt;strong&gt;Nizamuddin Auliya&lt;/strong&gt;, and his works reflect a deep spiritual essence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Options:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sanskrit and Tamil:&lt;/strong&gt; These languages have ancient roots and are unrelated to Khusrau&amp;rsquo;s works. They were primarily used for religious and classical literature in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bengali and Punjabi:&lt;/strong&gt; These regional languages have distinct literary traditions and were not influenced by Khusrau&amp;rsquo;s contributions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marathi and Gujarati:&lt;/strong&gt; These languages belong to different linguistic families and regions than those influenced by Khusrau.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Significance of Khusrau&amp;rsquo;s Work:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His innovative blending of Persian and Hindavi laid the foundation for the &lt;strong&gt;syncretic culture&lt;/strong&gt; of India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Through literature and music, Khusrau played a crucial role in fostering cultural harmony during his era.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His works continue to be celebrated in Indian classical music and poetry.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Governor.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The State Finance Commission is constituted by the Governor every five years.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The commission reviews the financial position of the Panchayats and Municipalities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It makes recommendations to the Governor regarding the distribution of financial resources.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Governor lays the recommendations before the State Legislature along with an explanatory memorandum.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Panchayati Raj Minister:&lt;/strong&gt; The Panchayati Raj Minister is responsible for the administration of Panchayats.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chief Minister:&lt;/strong&gt; The Chief Minister is the head of the state government.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker of Assembly:&lt;/strong&gt; The Speaker presides over the State Legislative Assembly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directive Principles of State Policy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the Constitution of India, promotion of international peace and security is included in the &amp;quot;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directive Principles of State Policy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 51&lt;/strong&gt; says&amp;nbsp;to promote&lt;strong&gt; international peace and security and maintain just and honourable relations between nations&lt;/strong&gt;. It is to foster respect for international law and treaty obligations and to encourage settlement of the international dispute by arbitration.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;These provisions are contained in Part IV (Article 36&amp;ndash;51) of the Constitution of India.&lt;/strong&gt; However, these are not enforceable by any court.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is the duty of the states&amp;nbsp;to consider Directive Principles while&amp;nbsp;making laws for the welfare of the people.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is taken from&amp;nbsp;the Constitution of Ireland.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The&amp;nbsp;Preamble of the Indian&amp;nbsp;Constitution&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;was adopted i.e. November 26, 1949.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The objectives&amp;nbsp;are to secure justice, liberty, equality to all citizens and promote fraternity to maintain unity and integrity of the nation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ninth Schedule&lt;/strong&gt; of the Indian Constitution contains a list of central and state laws which cannot be challenged in courts.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The fundamental duties are included in Article 51-A of the Indian Constitution&lt;/strong&gt;. There are 11 fundamental duties to which citizens must abide by.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jamner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The part of the peninsular plateau lying to the &lt;strong&gt;north of the Narmada river covering the major area of the malwa plateau is known as Central Highlands.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The flow of the rivers draining this region namely the Chambal, the Sindh, the betwa, and the ken is from southwest to northeast thus indicating the slope&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The plateau has three principal rivers: &lt;strong&gt;the Godavari, the Krishna, and the Kaveri&lt;/strong&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These rivers flow from the Western Ghats on the western side of the plateau eastward toward the Bay of Bengal, which is the largest bay in the world.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The part of the peninsular plateau lying to the north of the Narmada river covering the major area of the malwa plateau is known as Central Highlands.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The flow of the rivers draining this region namely &lt;strong&gt;the Chambal, the Sindh, the betwa, and the ken &lt;/strong&gt;is from southwest to northeast thus indicating the slope.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ganga and Brahmaputra flow eastward because of the gradient made by the Himalayas.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;They just follow the path which comes(from high altitude to low altitude), its general phenomenon of water flow and at last reach the Bay of Bengal which is at the lowest altitude.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4, i.e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Coromandel and Rayalaseema&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coromandel and Rayalaseema&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;of India receive the majority of their &lt;strong&gt;rainfall from the Northeast Monsoon&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While the southwest monsoon provides India with about 75 percent of the rainfall it receives, the northeastern monsoon brings substantial rainfall to &lt;strong&gt;Tamil Nadu, south-inner Karnataka, coastal Andhra Pradesh, Rayalaseema, Puducherry and Kerala.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A significant portion of Southern India relies on this monsoon and is vital to irrigation, groundwater recharging and reservoir filling for the summer of next year.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tamil Nadu&lt;/strong&gt;, the rain shadow area of the Western Ghats, receives just 35 percent of its annual rainfall from the Southwest Monsoon. The winter or northeast monsoon provides 48 percent of the annual rainfall to the state.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;<br><br><p>সঠিক উত্তর হল <strong>Option 4, অর্থাৎ </strong><strong><u>করমণ্ডল এবং রায়লসীমা</u></strong>।</p>

<p><span style="display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;"><img height="26px" src="//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png" width="26px" /><strong><span style="vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;"><u>গুরুত্বপূর্ণ বিষয়</u></span></strong></span></p>

<ul>
	<li>ভারতের <strong>করমণ্ডল এবং রায়লসীমা</strong> অঞ্চল তাদের অধিকাংশ <strong>বৃষ্টিপাত উত্তর-পূর্ব মৌসুমী বায়ু</strong> থেকে লাভ করে।</li>
	<li>দক্ষিণ-পশ্চিম মৌসুমী বায়ু ভারত যে বৃষ্টিপাত পায় তার প্রায় 75 শতাংশ সরবরাহ করে, উত্তর-পূর্ব মৌসুমী বায়ু <strong>তামিলনাড়ু, দক্ষিণ-অভ্যন্তরীণ কর্ণাটক, উপকূলীয় অন্ধ্র প্রদেশ, রায়লসীমা, পুদুচেরি এবং কেরালাকে</strong> যথেষ্ট বৃষ্টিপাত দেয়।</li>
	<li>দক্ষিণ ভারতের একটি উল্লেখযোগ্য অংশ এই মৌসুমী বায়ুর উপর নির্ভর করে এবং এটি পরবর্তী বছরের গ্রীষ্মের জন্য সেচ, ভূগর্ভস্থ জল রিচার্জ এবং জলাধার পূরণের জন্য অত্যাবশ্যক।</li>
	<li><strong>তামিলনাড়ু</strong>, পশ্চিমঘাট পর্বতমালার বৃষ্টিচ্ছায় অঞ্চল, তার বার্ষিক বৃষ্টিপাতের মাত্র 35 শতাংশ দক্ষিণ-পশ্চিম মৌসুমী বায়ু থেকে পায়। শীতকালীন বা উত্তর-পূর্ব মৌসুমী বায়ু রাজ্যটিকে বার্ষিক বৃষ্টিপাতের 48 শতাংশ সরবরাহ করে।</li>
</ul>

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Taiga ecosystem&lt;/strong&gt; is an example of a&lt;strong&gt; &lt;u&gt;forest ecosystem.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Taiga also called&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Boreal forest,&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;biome (major life zone) of vegetation composed primarily of cone-bearing needle-leaved or scale-leaved evergreen trees, found in northern circumpolar forested regions characterized by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;long winters&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;moderate to high annual precipitation&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The taiga,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span dir=&quot;RTL&quot;&gt;&amp;ldquo;&lt;/span&gt;land of the little sticks&amp;rdquo; in Russian, takes its name from the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-darkreader-inline-color=&quot;&quot;&gt;collective&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;term for the northern forests of Russia, especially Siberia.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;horse latitudes are regions located at about 30 degrees north and south of the equator.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;About Taiga&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;They are tall, softwood evergreen trees. The woods of these trees are very useful for making pulp, which is used for manufacturing paper and newsprint.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Chir, pine, cedar&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the important variety of trees in these forests.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Silver fox, mink, polar bear are the common animals found here.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Black soil&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is best suited for the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;cultivation of the cotton&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;because Black soil&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;holds moisture&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;for longer periods and possess rich quantities of humus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Besides cotton, the Black soil is suitable for the cultivation of crops like&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Wheat, Groundnut, Chillies, Tobacco and Jowar&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;which is found in the region of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Deccan and Malwa Plateau&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;India is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;second-largest producer of cotton&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the world which is a Kharif fiber crop that requires high temperature and rainfall of about 50-120 cm and can be grown in the region of Deccan Plateau as well as up to some extent in alluvial soils of the Satluj-Ganga plain and red and laterite soils of the peninsular region.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;China leads the world in cotton production&lt;/span&gt;, followed by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;India&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;United States&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;while China is simultaneously the largest importer of cotton whereas the USA is the largest exporter of cotton.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Power.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shutting down a PC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To&lt;strong&gt; turn off your PC in Windows 10,&lt;/strong&gt; select the &lt;strong&gt;Start button, select the Power button, and then select Shut down.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Shutting down your computer is when all the &lt;strong&gt;software, programs, files,&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;processes&lt;/strong&gt; are closed and &lt;strong&gt;the memory in the RAM is cleared.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Before &lt;strong&gt;shutting down&lt;/strong&gt; it is important to save all your work as your computer &lt;strong&gt;will not re-open&lt;/strong&gt; anything you were previously working on &lt;strong&gt;before shutting down.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is best to &lt;strong&gt;shut down your computer&lt;/strong&gt; when you don&amp;rsquo;t need to use it for a while and&lt;strong&gt; to save power.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shutting down&lt;/strong&gt; your computer also allows it to&lt;strong&gt; run faster with a clear RAM.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sleep mode&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a &lt;strong&gt;power-saving mode &lt;/strong&gt;that stores all of your &lt;strong&gt;open files, software, &lt;/strong&gt;and other data in the &lt;strong&gt;computer&amp;rsquo;s main memory, or RAM.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;During sleep mode,&lt;strong&gt; the rest of your computer shuts down besides the RAM&lt;/strong&gt;, which continues to draw power from the battery outlet.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Everything you were previously working on remains open and can be pulled up when you &lt;strong&gt;open up your laptop or press the power button.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sleep mode&lt;/strong&gt; is best used when you need to step away from your&lt;strong&gt; computer for a moment &lt;/strong&gt;but will come back to it within a few hours.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hibernate mode&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is similar to sleep mode with the exception that &lt;strong&gt;your computer completely shuts down and draws no power, unlike sleep mode.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Everything you previously had open and running is&lt;strong&gt; stored in a hibernation file on your hard drive.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When you open your laptop or&lt;strong&gt; turn the screen back on your computer everything will be just as you left it.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hibernate mode &lt;/strong&gt;is best used when you don&amp;rsquo;t need to access your computer for a while or if you won&amp;rsquo;t have access to a power source later on and need &lt;strong&gt;to save battery life.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It provides access to open and frequently used programs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The taskbar is a primary feature of the Windows desktop interface that provides quick access to open programs and frequently used applications.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It contains the &amp;quot;Start&amp;quot; button, which opens the Start Menu, allowing users to search for and launch installed programs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Users can pin their favorite applications to the taskbar for easy access, reducing the need to navigate through directories.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The taskbar also displays active programs, enabling users to switch between them using simple clicks.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Additional features include the system tray, where users can view notifications and access background-running programs like antivirus software, Wi-Fi, and volume controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Taskbar Terminology:&lt;/strong&gt; The taskbar consists of key components such as the Start button, pinned apps, active program icons, and the system tray.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customizability:&lt;/strong&gt; Users can customize the taskbar by resizing it, changing its position (top, bottom, left, or right of the screen), and choosing which icons are displayed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multi-Monitor Support:&lt;/strong&gt; In Windows 10 and later versions, the taskbar can be extended across multiple monitors, providing flexibility for users working on multi-screen setups.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Search Bar Integration:&lt;/strong&gt; The taskbar often integrates with a search bar, enabling users to perform quick searches for files, settings, or web content directly from the desktop.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evolution Over Time:&lt;/strong&gt; The taskbar has evolved significantly since its introduction in Windows 95, incorporating features like Cortana, virtual desktops, and app previews in newer versions of Windows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Windows Media Player&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Windows Media Player&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is software is used for running&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;MP4 files&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;on a computer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MP4 files:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A file with the .mp4&amp;nbsp;file extension&amp;nbsp;is a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;MPEG-4 video file format.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MP4s are one of the more common video file formats used for downloading and streaming&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;videos&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;from the internet.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s a&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;highly versatile and compressed video format&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;that also can store audio, subtitles, and still images.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The current and the latest version&amp;mdash;&lt;strong&gt;MPEG-4 Part 14&amp;mdash;was released in 2003.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;With the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;high degree of compression&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;used in MP4 videos, this&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;allows the files to be much smaller in size&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;than other video formats.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Almost all of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;original quality is retained&lt;/strong&gt;. This makes MP4 a portable and web-friendly video format.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

